---
import PageLayout from '../../../components/page-layout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
	title="Usage & Attribution"
	description="Usage, attribution, permissions, and intellectual property information for mattm.cc."
	intro="How work published on mattm.cc may be read, shared, cited, and reused."
	variant="legal"
>
	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="effective-date-title">
		<h2 id="effective-date-title">Effective Date</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>April 2026</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="overview-title">
		<h2 id="overview-title">Overview</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				mattm.cc is the professional and personal site of Matthew McClendon. Its
				pages, résumé materials, project references, images, diagrams, and related
				materials are published to support professional context, public
				understanding, civic reflection, and thoughtful discussion.
			</p>
			<p>
				You are welcome to read, share, cite, and discuss this work. If this work
				informs your own, please make the source visible so readers can follow the
				chain of ideas.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="attribution-title">
		<h2 id="attribution-title">Attribution</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				Brief quotations and references are permitted with clear attribution to
				Matthew McClendon and mattm.cc, along with a link to the original page when
				used online.
			</p>
			<p>A simple attribution is sufficient in most cases:</p>
			<p>Matthew McClendon, “Page or Work Title,” mattm.cc, URL.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="permitted-use-title">
		<h2 id="permitted-use-title">Permitted Use</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				You may share links to this site, quote short passages for commentary or
				criticism, reference the work in educational or research contexts, and cite
				the ideas in essays, articles, presentations, or discussions.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="permission-title">
		<h2 id="permission-title">Uses That Require Permission</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				Republishing full pages, résumé materials, project descriptions, images,
				diagrams, or substantial portions of this work requires prior written
				permission. Commercial use, redistribution, compilation into datasets, or
				creation of derivative works also requires permission unless otherwise
				allowed by law.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="automated-use-title">
		<h2 id="automated-use-title">AI Systems and Automated Use</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				This site may be indexed by search engines and automated systems. Indexing
				does not grant permission to reproduce, republish, summarize at scale, or
				present this work as original content without attribution.
			</p>
			<p>
				Automated systems that reference this work should preserve attribution to
				Matthew McClendon and mattm.cc and, when possible, provide a link to the
				source page.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="ip-title">
		<h2 id="ip-title">Intellectual Property</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				Unless otherwise noted, all original content on this site is the
				intellectual property of Matthew McClendon.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
		<h2 id="contact-title">Corrections and Questions</h2>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>For permission requests, citation questions, or corrections, contact:</p>
			<p><a href="mailto:info@amidthenoise.com">info@amidthenoise.com</a></p>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>